SIGN function

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| SIGN(number)                                                                |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Returns -1 if the number is less than 0, 0 if it is 0, or 1 if it is more than
0.

Examples:

	SIGN('l2.3')    == 1
	SIGN(0.0)       == 0
	SIGN(' -0.307') == -1
